messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path
- /login

All HTTP methods acceptable?
- No

HTTP methods accepted (based on the code)
- HEAD: No (not explicitly mapped)
- POST: Yes (method = RequestMethod.POST on @RequestMapping(value = "/login"))
- OPTIONS: Yes (there is a controller-level @RequestMapping(method = RequestMethod.OPTIONS, value = "/*") which covers /login)
- TRACE: No (not explicitly mapped)
- GET: No (no @RequestMapping for GET at /login)
- PUT: No (not explicitly mapped)
- DELETE: No (not explicitly mapped)
- PATCH: No (not explicitly mapped)

Explanation
- The login handler is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/login", method = RequestMethod.POST), so POST to /login is explicitly supported.
- There is a general OPTIONS handler annotated @RequestMapping(method = RequestMethod.OPTIONS, value = "/*"). The "/*" pattern matches top-level paths such as /login, so OPTIONS requests to /login are handled by handleOptions and therefore accepted.
- No @RequestMapping exists for GET, HEAD, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, or TRACE on /login in the provided code. Per your instruction to base acceptability on the code (not on framework implicit behavior), those methods are considered not acceptable.
